{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Conversation history is trimmed to the most recent 10 messages before the LLM call when history is too long.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: A unit test of the trim helper can pass while call-site wiring still sends untrimmed history. REAL-INFRA: No OS/network needed. MOCK-HIDE: In-process fake LLM that captures payload is enough, but test must span request handler + prompt builder + LLM client boundary. LLM-DEP: No. MULTI-STEP: No.","test_description":"Run the chatbot request path with 15 prior messages using a capturing fake LLM client; assert the actual payload sent to the client contains exactly the last 10 messages in correct order, and older 5 are absent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Generated response addresses the customer’s question (not generic/off-topic).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Pure mocks cannot reveal semantic relevance failures. REAL-INFRA: External API may be used, but core risk is model output quality variance. MOCK-HIDE: Mocked model would always look relevant if scripted. LLM-DEP: Yes, correctness depends on real model judgment/generation and can vary run-to-run. MULTI-STEP: Single agentic quality gate is sufficient.","test_description":"Use real LLM generation on a fixed set of representative customer questions and evaluate relevance with a rubric/model-judge threshold; fail when responses are generic/off-topic beyond allowed rate across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.2}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Tone re-check detects overly formal response for casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Mocking tone decisions misses true misclassification/regeneration behavior. REAL-INFRA: Could run via API, but key boundary is chained model behavior. MOCK-HIDE: If tone-check is mocked to 'formal', regen path always passes. LLM-DEP: Yes, tone judgment is model-dependent. MULTI-STEP: Requires sequential agentic steps (initial response -> tone judgment -> regenerated response).","test_description":"Execute end-to-end with real model calls: provide casual-tier prompt likely to induce formal first draft, verify tone-check flags it, verify a second generation occurs, and verify second output is accepted under tone criteria.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.35,"Workflow":0.55}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Full exchange (user message, initial response, regenerations) is persisted with correct timestamps.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Unit tests can miss ORM/transaction/schema mapping issues. REAL-INFRA: Needs real local DB interaction; external OS/network not required. MOCK-HIDE: Mock repository can hide timestamp/default-column bugs. LLM-DEP: No. MULTI-STEP: No agentic sequence required for this assertion.","test_description":"Use a real test database, execute one conversation including forced regeneration path, then query persisted records and assert all entries exist, are linked to the conversation, and timestamps are correctly populated and ordered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If tone check triggers regeneration, only the second response is shown to the customer; rejected draft is never exposed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: A unit test of selector logic can miss handler/streaming orchestration leaks. REAL-INFRA: Usually no external infra required if tested through app boundary with fakes. MOCK-HIDE: Must avoid mocking the presentation layer too narrowly or leak bugs are missed. LLM-DEP: Not inherently; trigger can be forced. MULTI-STEP: Sequence exists, but agentic realism is not required to validate visibility control.","test_description":"Run request through API/service boundary with controlled first/second model outputs and forced tone-trigger; assert client-visible payload/event stream contains only second response while first is retained only in internal logs/audit fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.25}}]}
